author: COMSOL
description:
This example is built from a supplied geometry model file which contains geometry parts to build baffled flat and dished bottom mixers with either a pitched blade impeller or a Rushton turbine. The model features a simulation of turbulent flow in a dished bottom vessel with a pitched blade impeller using the k-omega model.

The example uses the Frozen Rotor simulation method, for which the rotating parts are kept frozen in position together with the vessel wall and baffles, and the rotation is accounted for by the inclusion of centrifugal and Coriolis forces.
